    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate for **Ghost Ride the WHIP** is headlined by the speed-oriented upside of **Jose Caballero** (77.16) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.97). **Jose Caballero** is our premium play against Springs, as his dynamic platoon advantage (+13%) and the high-probability steal environment created by Springs' slow delivery outweigh the suboptimal #8 lineup slot. Meanwhile, **Mickey Moniak** benefits from a massive SP skill boost (+19%) against the shaky V\u00e1squez, combined with a highly favorable #2 spot in the order. In the heart of the lineup, **Giancarlo Stanton** (67.71) remains a mandatory start; his elite 14% skill edge against the lefty Springs and prime cleanup duties make him our most bankable source of power.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the morning was opting for **Max Muncy** (61.96) over our depth options. **Max Muncy** gained significant traction today due to a rare platoon-neutralizing effect and the stolen base potential against a pitcher with a slow delivery profile; while he isn't a traditional speed threat, the total efficiency score narrowly eclipsed our internal threshold for substitution. Among the bench, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** was the strongest consideration, but his status as a non-starter today renders his high raw projection moot, effectively locking him into a zero. We remain cautious with **Vinnie Pasquantino** (51.61) at Utility; while the 5% wind-out factor is a nice perk, his -15% platoon penalty against Kay limits his ceiling to marginal status, and he is the first candidate we would swap should late-breaking lineup news change the projected order for **Tyler Soderstrom** or **Zach McKinstry**. We are monitoring the **Tyler Soderstrom** matchup closely, as his -6% platoon drag against Weathers leaves him hovering just above our \"Below floor\" limit.",
